obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4065)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 1st April, 1991, vide notification No. G.S.R 253, dated 27th March, 1991, see Gazette of India Ordinary, Part II sec. 3(i).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4065&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Public Liability Insurance Act,`
  line 1991.
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4066)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4066&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) "accident" means an accident involving a fortuitous or sudden or unintended occurrence`
  line `while handling any hazardous substance resulting in continuous or intermittent or repeated exposure`
  line `to death of, or injury to, any person or damage to any property but does not include an accident by`
  line `reason only of war or radio-activity;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Collector" means the Collector having jurisdiction over the area in which the accident`
  line occurs;
  line
  line `(c) "handling", in relation to any hazardous substance, means the manufacture, processing,`
  line `treatment, package, storage, transportation by vehicle, use, collection, destruction, conversion,`
  line `offering for sale, transfer or the like of such hazardous substance;`
  line
  line `(d) "hazardous substance" means any substance or preparation which is defined as hazardous`
  line `substance under the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986), and exceeding such quantity as`
  line `may be specified, by notification, by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) "insurance" means insurance against liability under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the official Gazette;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `(g) "owner" means a person who owns, or has control over handling, any hazardous substance`
  line `at the time of accident and includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of firm, any of its partners;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an association, any of its members; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a company, any of its directors, managers, secretaries or other officers who`
  line `is directly in charge of, and is responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the`
  line company;]
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(ha) "property" includes any private property or public property affected or damaged by any`
  line `unit or undertaking, due to manufacture, processing, treatment, package, storage, transportation, use,`
  line `collection, destruction, conversion, transfer or such other processes of hazardous substance;]`
  line
  line ^4[
  line `^5[(hb)] "Relief Fund" means the Environmental Relief Fund established under section 7A";`
  line
  line `(i) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "vehicle" means any mode of surface transport other than railways.`
  line
  line `^6[(k) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Transfer of`
  line `Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), and the Environment (Protection) Act,1986 (29 of 1986), shall have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (g) (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 2, (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (ha) shall be renumbered as clause (hb) thereof by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4067)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Liability to give relief in certain cases on principle of no fault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4067&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^2[(1) Where death or injury to`
  line `any person (other than a workman) or damage to any property has resulted from an accident, the owner`
  line `shall be liable to reimburse such amount, or provide such other relief as may be prescribed, for--`
  line
  line `(a) death due to fatal accident;`
  line
  line `(b) medical expenses incurred due to total or partial disability;`
  line
  line `(c) loss of wages due to partial disability;`
  line
  line `(d) other injury or sickness;`
  line
  line `(e) damage to private property;`
  line
  line or
  line
  line `(f) such other loss or damage, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) In any claim for relief under sub-section (1) (hereinafter referred to in this Act as claim for relief),`
  line `the claimant shall not be required to plead and establish that the death, injury or damage in respect of`
  line `which the claim has been made was due to any wrongful act, neglect or default of any person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "workman" has the meaning assigned to it in the Workmens Compensation Act, 1923`
  line `(8 of 1923);`
  line
  line `(ii) "injury" includes permanent total or permanent partial disability or sickness resulting out of`
  line `an accident.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4068)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Duty of owner to take out insurance policies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4068&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every owner of any undertaking shall take`
  line `out, before he starts handling any hazardous substance, one or more insurance policies for such undertaking or unit providing for contracts of insurance whereby he is insured against liability to give such relief or reimburse such amount referred to in sub-section (1) of section 3.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, it is hereby clarified that any undertaking having`
  line `separate consent to operate under--`
  line
  line `(i) the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974); and`
  line
  line `(ii) the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1981 (14 of 1981), shall be treated as a`
  line `separate unit:`
  line
  line `Provided that any owner handling any hazardous substance immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the Jan Vishwas (Amendment of Provisions) Act, 2023 shall take out such insurance policy or policies as`
  line `soon as may be and in any case within a period of one year from commencement of that Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner shall get the insurance policy, referred to in sub-section (1), renewed from time to`
  line `time before the expiry of the period of validity thereof so that the insurance policies may remain in force`
  line `throughout the period during which such handling is continued.`
  line
  line `^2[ ^3[(2A) An insurance policy taken out or renewed by an owner for any undertaking or unit shall be for an amount which shall not be less than the amount of the paid-up capital of that undertaking or unit handling any hazardous substance owned or controlled by that owner and may extend to such amount as may be prescribed but not exceeding five hundred crore rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section "paid-up capital", in relation to an owner not being a company, means the market value of all assets and stocks of the undertaking on the date of`
  line `contract of insurance.]`
  line
  line `(2B) The liability of the insurer under one assurance policy shall not exceed the amount specified in`
  line `the terms of the contract of insurance in that insurance policy.`
  line
  line `(2C) Every owner shall also, together with the amount of premium, pay to the insurer, for being credited to the Relief Fund established under section 7A, such further amount, not exceeding the sum equivalent to the amount of premium, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2D) The insurer shall remit to the authority specified in sub-section (3) of section 7A the amount received from the owner under sub-section (2C) for being credited to the Relief Fund in such manner and within such period as may be prescribed and where the insurer fails to so remit the amount, it shall be recoverable from insurer as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.]`
  line
  line `(3)The Central Government may, by notification, exempt from the operation of sub-section (1) any owner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any State Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any corporation owned or controlled by the Central Government or a State Government; or`
  line
  line `(d) any local authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made in relation to such owner unless a fund has been established and is maintained by that owner in accordance with the rules made in this behalf for meeting any liability under sub-section (1) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2013, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4069)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Verification and publication of accident by Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4069&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it comes to the notice of the`
  line `Collector that an accident has occurred at any place within his jurisdiction, he shall verify the occurrence of such accident and cause publicity to be given in such manner as he deems fit for inviting applications`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4070)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Application for claim for relief.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4070&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for claim for relief may be made`
  line
  line `(a) by the person who has sustained the injury;`
  line
  line `(b) by the owner of the property to which the damage has been caused;`
  line
  line `(c) where death has resulted from the accident, by all or any of the legal representatives of the`
  line `deceased; or`
  line
  line `(d) by any agent duly authorised by such person or owner of such property or all or any of the`
  line `legal representatives of the deceased, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where all the legal representatives of the deceased have not joined in any such`
  line `application for relief, the application shall be made on behalf of or for the benefit of all the legal`
  line `representatives of the deceased and the legal representatives who have not so joined shall be impleaded as`
  line `respondents to the application.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made to the Collector and shall be in such form,`
  line `contain such particulars and shall be accompanied by such documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No application for relief shall be entertained unless it is made within five years of the occurrence`
  line `of the accident.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4071)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Award of relief.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4071&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1) of section 6, the Collector`
  line `shall, after giving notice of the application to the owner and after giving the parties an opportunity of`
  line `being heard, hold an inquiry into the claim or, each of the claims, and may make an award determining`
  line `the amount of relief which appears to him to be just and specifying the person or persons to whom such`
  line `amount of relief shall be paid.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector shall arrange to deliver copies of the award to the parties concerned expeditiously`
  line `and in any case within a period of fifteen days from the date of the award.`
  line
  line ^1[
  line `(3) When an award is made under this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the insurer, who is required to pay any amount in terms of such award and to the extent`
  line `specified in sub-section (2B) of section 4, shall, within a period of thirty days of the date of`
  line `announcement of the award, deposit that amount in such manner as the Collector may direct;`
  line
  line `(b) the Collector shall arrange to pay from the Relief Fund, in terms of such award and in`
  line `accordance with the scheme made under section 7A, to the person or persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) such amount as may be specified in that scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) the owner shall, within such period, deposit such amount in such manner as the Collector may`
  line direct.]
  line
  line `(4) In holding any inquiry under sub-section (1), the Collector may, subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf, follow such summary procedure as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The Collector shall have all the powers of Civil Court for the purpose of taking evidence on oath`
  line `and of enforcing the attendance of witnesses and of compelling the discovery and production of`
  line `documents and material objects and for such other purposes as may be prescribed;`
  line `and the Collector shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter`
  line `XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure,1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(6) Where the insurer or the owner against whom the award is made under sub-section (1) fails to`
  line `deposit the amount of such award within the period specified under sub-section (3), such amount shall be`
  line `recoverable from the owner, or as the case may be, the insurer as arrears of land revenue or of public`
  line demand.
  line
  line `(7) A claim for relief in respect of death of, or injury to, any person or damage to any property shall`
  line `be disposed of as expeditiously as possible and every endeavour shall be made to dispose of such claim`
  line `within three months of the receipt of the application for relief under sub-section (1) of section 6.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `(8) Where an owner is likely to remove or dispose of his property with the object of evading`
  line `payment by him of any amount of award, the Collector may, in accordance with the provisions of rules 1`
  line `to 4 of Order XXXIX of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), grant a`
  line `temporary injunction to restrain such act.]`
  line
  line `^3[(9) Where the environment is affected or damaged due to manufacture, processing, treatment,`
  line `package, storage, transportation, use, collection, destruction, conversion, transfer or such other processes,`
  line `of such hazardouss substance, the Central Government may, on an application made by the Central`
  line `Pollution Control Board or the State Pollution Control Board, as the case may be, allocate the fund from`
  line `the Environmental Relief Fund for restoration of the damage so caused in the manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (4072)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Establishment of Environmental Relief Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4072&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ 7A. Establishment of Environmental Relief Fund.(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, establish a fund to be known as the Environmental Relief Fund.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) There shall be credited to the Relief Fund established under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount referred to in sub-section (2C) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of penalty imposed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the interest or other income received out of investments made from the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other amount from such sources, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Relief Fund shall be utilised for paying, in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `scheme made under sub-section (3),relief under the award made by the Collector under section 7.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, make a scheme specifying the authority in which`
  line `the Relief Fund shall vest, the manner in which the Relief Fund shall be administered, the form and the`
  line `manner in which money shall be drawn from the Relief Fund and for all other matters connected with or`
  line `incidental to the administration of the Relief Fund and the payment of relief therefrom.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 5, (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4073)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Provisions as to other right to claim compensation for death, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4073&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right to claim relief`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 in respect of death of, or injury to, any person or damage to any`
  line `property shall be in addition to any other right to claim compensation in respect thereof under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where in respect of death of, or injury to,`
  line `any person or damage to any property, the owner, liable to give claim for relief, is also liable to pay`
  line `compensation under any other law, the amount of such compensation shall be reduced by the amount of`
  line `relief paid under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4074)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4074&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Any person authorised by the Central Government may, for the`
  line `purposes of ascertaining whether any requirements of this Act or of any rule or of any direction given`
  line `under this Act have been compiled with, require any owner to submit to that person such information as`
  line `that person may reasonably think necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4075)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4075&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any person, authorised by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, shall have a right to enter, at all reasonable times with such assistance as he considers necessary,`
  line `any place, premises or vehicle, where hazardous substance is handled for the purpose of determining`
  line `whether any provisions of this Act or of any rule or of any direction given under this Act is being or has`
  line `been compiled with and such owner is bound to render all assistance to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4076)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4076&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person, authorised by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, has reason to believe that handling of any hazardous substance is taking place in any place,`
  line `premises or vehicle, in contravention of sub-section (1) of section 4, he may enter into and search such`
  line `place, premises or vehicle for such handling of hazardous substance.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, as a result of any search under sub-section (1) any handling of hazardous substance has`
  line `been found in relation to which contravention of sub-section (1) of section 4 has taken place, he may seize`
  line `such hazardous substance and other things which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or relevant to, any`
  line `proceeding under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any such substance or thing, he may serve on the`
  line `owner an order that the owner shall not remove, part with, or otherwise deal with, the hazardous`
  line `substance and such other things except with the previous permission of that person.`
  line
  line `(3) He may, if he has reason to believe that it is expedient so to do to prevent an accident dispose of`
  line `the hazardous substance seized under sub-section (2) immediately in such manner as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred by him in the disposal of hazardous substances under sub-section (3) shall`
  line `be recoverable from the owner as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4077)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4077&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law but subject to`
  line `the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, in exercise of its powers and performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act, issue such directions in writing as it may deem fit for the purposes of this Act to`
  line `any owner or any person, officer, authority or agency and such owner, person, officer, authority or agency`
  line `shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibition or regulation of the handling of any hazardous substance; or`
  line
  line `(b) stoppage or regulation of the supply of electricity, water or any other service`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4078)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make application to Courts for restraining owner from handling hazardous substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4078&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government or any person authorised by that Government in this behalf`
  line `has reason to believe that any owner has been handling any hazardous substance in contravention of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act, that Government or, as the case may be, that person may make an`
  line `application to a Court, not inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate first class`
  line `for restraining such owner from such handling.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the application under sub-section (1), the Court may make such order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where under sub-section (2), the Court makes an order restraining any owner from handling`
  line `hazardous substance, it may, in that order--`
  line
  line `(a) direct such owner to desist from such handling;`
  line
  line `(b) authorise the Central Government or, as the case may be, the person referred to in`
  line `sub-section(1), if the direction under clause (a) is not complied with by the owner to whom such`
  line `direction is issued, to implement the direction in such manner as may be specified by the Court.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred by the Central Government, or as the case may be, the person in`
  line `implementing the directions of Court under clause (b) of sub-section (3), shall be recoverable from the`
  line `owner as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4079)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Penalty for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4079&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Penalty for contravention.-- (1) Where any person contravenes any of the provisions of sub-section (1), sub-section (2), sub-section (2A) or sub-section (2C) of section 4, he shall be liable to penalty equal to the amount of annual premium for insurance policy and may extend to twice the amount`
  line `of such premium.`
  line
  line `(2) Where contravention under subsection (1) continues, an additional penalty may be imposed by the adjudicating officer, which shall not exceed the amount of premium to be paid, for each month or part thereof during which the contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4080)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for non-compliance of directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4080&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Penalty for non-compliance of directions.--(1) Where any person does not comply with any direction issued under section 12, he shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues non-compliance under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to additional`
  line `penalty to be imposed by the adjudicating officer, which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees for`
  line `every day during which such non-compliance continues.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any owner does not comply with the direction issued under section 9 or obstructs any`
  line `person in discharge of his functions under section 10 or under sub-sections (1), (2) or (3) of section 11, he`
  line `shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to fifteen`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any person continues non-compliance under sub-section (3), he shall be liable to additional`
  line `penalty of ten thousand rupees for every day during which such non-compliance continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (89163)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 17
  title `Adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=89163&sectionno=15A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Adjudicating officer.--(1) The Central Government, for the purposes of determining the penalties under sections 14 or 15, may appoint the District Magistrate having jurisdiction over the area or an officer not below the rank of Director to the Government of India or an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the State Government, to be the adjudicating officer, to hold an inquiry and impose penalty in the manner, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may appoint as many adjudicating officers as may be required`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may summon and enforce the attendance of any person acquainted with`
  line `the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion`
  line `of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject matter of the inquiry and if, on`
  line `such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has failed to comply with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), sub-section (2), sub-section (2A) or sub-section (2C) of section 4 and section 12, he may`
  line `determine such penalty as he thinks fit under the provisions of sections 14 and 15:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed without giving the person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (89164)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 18
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for section 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=89164&sectionno=15B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Appeal.--(1) Whoever aggrieved by the order, passed by the adjudicating officer under section`
  line `15A, may prefer an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal is preferred against any order of the adjudicating officer under sub-section (1), such appeal shall not be entertained by the Tribunal unless such person has deposited with the Tribunal ten per cent. of the amount of the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4081)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title Omitted.
  content `[Offences by companies.]--Omitted by the Jan Vishwas (Amendment of Provisions) Act, 2023 (18 of 2023), s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4081&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4082)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalty for contravention by Government Department.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4082&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where an offence under this Act has been committed`
  line `by any Department of Government, the Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (89165)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 21
  title `Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Relief Fund.`
  content `^1[17A. Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Relief Fund.--Where any penalty or additional penalty, as the case may be, is imposed under section 14 or section 15 or section 17, the amount of such penalty shall be credited to the Environmental Relief Fund established under section 7A.]`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sections 14 and 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=89165&sectionno=17A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_17_b:
  sectionId (89166)
  sectionNo 17B
  orderNo 22
  title `Offence for failure to pay penalty or additional penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for section 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=89166&sectionno=17B&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[17B. Offence for failure to pay penalty or additional penalty.--(1) Where any person fails to pay the penalty or additional penalty imposed for--`
  line
  line `(a) contravention or continued contravention under section 14 or 17, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) non-compliance of the directions issued under section 15, within ninety days of such imposition, he shall be liable for imprisonment which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend up to fifteen lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any offence under subsection (1) has been committed by a company, every person who, at`
  line `the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of such`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director,`
  line
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer`
  line `shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director" includes director of the company and in relation to a firm, a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4083)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4083&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act except on`
  line `a complaint made by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or any authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has given notice of not less than sixty days in the manner prescribed, of the`
  line `alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint, to the Central Government or the authority`
  line `or officer authorised as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4084)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4084&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, delegate, subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations as may be specified in the notification, such of its powers and functions under`
  line `this Act (except the power under section 23) as it may deem necessary or expedient to any person`
  line `(including any officer, authority or other agency).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4085)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4085&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or the person, officer, authority or other agency in respect of anything which`
  line `is done or intended to be done in good faith in pursuance of this Act or the rules made or orders or`
  line `directions issued thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4086)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4086&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to time, constitute an`
  line `Advisory Committee on the matters relating to the insurance policy under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Committee shall consist of`
  line
  line `(a) three officers representing the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) two persons representing the insurers;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons representing the owners; and`
  line
  line `(d) two persons from amongst the experts of insurance or hazardous substances.`
  line `to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman of the Advisory Committee shall be one of the members representing the Central`
  line `Government, nominated in this behalf by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4087)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4087&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act and any rules made thereunder shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4088)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502&sectionId=4088&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00006_199106_1517807323502
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely--`
  line
  line `^1[^2[(a) such amount under subsection (2A) of section 4;]`
  line
  line `(aa) the amount required to be paid by every owner for being credited to the Relief Fund under`
  line `sub-section (2C) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ab) the manner in which and the period within which the amount received from the owner is`
  line `required to be remitted by the insurer under sub-section (2D) of section 4;`
  line
  line `^3[(ac)] establishment and maintenance of fund under sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of application and the particulars to be given therein and the documents to`
  line `accompany such application under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure for holding an inquiry under sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the purposes for which the Collector shall have powers of a Civil Court under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 7;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which notice of the offence and of the intention to make a complaint to the`
  line `Central Government shall be given under clause (b) of section 18;`
  line
  line `^4[(ea) amount or relief and any other loss or damage under subsection (1) of section 3`
  line
  line `(eb) such other person under sub-section (1A) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(ec) manner of allocation of fund for restoration of damage under sub-section (9) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(ed) any other amount from other sources under clause (d) of subsection (1A) of section 7A;`
  line
  line `(ee) manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under subsection (1) of section 15A;]`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every ^5[ rule or scheme] made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the ^5[`
  line `rule or scheme] or both Houses agree that the ^3[`
  line `rule or scheme] should not be made,`
  line `the ^5[`
  line `rule or scheme] shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that ^5[`
  line `rule or scheme].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (a) shall be re-lettered as clause (ac) by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 1992, s. 7, for "rule" (w.e.f. 31-1-1992).`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `लोक दायित्‍व बीमा अधिनियम, 1991`
